<p>I would like to use tcp-mss option of iptables.  I have a private lan behind my gateway and I would like to set MSS value of all tcp connections from the local lan to 1300. </p>  <p>I used below IP table rule on Gateway machine.</p>  <p>iptables -t mangle -A POSTROUTING -p tcp --tcp-flags SYN,RST SYN -o eth0 -j TCPMSS --set-mss 1300 -s 172.16.28.0/24</p>  <p>I see that the SYN packets are set with MSS value of 1300, but the SYN,ACK packet is set with more than 1300 ( more than 1400) . Because of this the after the initial packets transferred, the connection drops and not data transfer is done. </p>  <p>11:16:46.219836 IP xxxx.48670 > m.heise.de.http: Flags [S], seq 4060171724, win 65535, options [mss 1300,sackOK,TS val 1671995 ecr 0,nop,wscale 8], length 0</p>  <p>11:16:46.226467 IP m.heise.de.http > xxxx.48665: Flags [S.], seq 2078178562, ack 2812151753, win 3900, options [mss 1452,nop,nop,TS val 63595048 ecr 1671995,sackOK,eol], length 0</p>  <p>Did I missed anything (any IP table rule) ? </p>